text: The West Channel Pile Light is an active two-storey octagonal lighthouse in Port Phillip, Victoria, Australia. It was built in 1881, replacing a lightship installed in 1854, to mark the north-east end of the West Sand. The site is listed in the Victorian Heritage Register. ==See also== * South Channel Pile Light * List of lighthouses in Australia ==References== Category:Lighthouses completed in 1881 Category:Port Phillip Category:Lighthouses in Victoria (Australia) Category:Victorian Heritage Register Category:1881 establishments in Australia
